heaviest_rainfall.status: 22.76mm of rain was recorded as having fallen today, marking an exceptional precipitation event and it ranked 7th out of our records.  A rate of 8.3mm per hour was recorded during the 29.3 hour long storm.  Record-breaking rain fell on 09 November 2025 with a total accumulation of 47.89mm over 144.8 hours and falling at a rate of 24.6mm per hour at times.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The heaviest rain was recorded on 02 September 2025 with a peak rate of 34.3mm per hour.  The storm lasted 15.0 hours and had a total rainfall of 21.19mm.

longest_rain.status: Today, one rain storm lasted for 29.3 hours (ranking 7th for longest storm from our records).  It accumulated 22.76mm of rain and it fell at 8.3mm per hour at times.  Rain fell for 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 47.89mm with a maximum intensity of 24.6mm per hour.
